text: Azovo (Russian: Азово, German: Asowo) is a rural locality (a selo). It is also the administrative center of Azovsky Nemetsky National District of Omsk Oblast, Russia. ==Population== Population of Azovo is mostly German spoken. Half of the population has got German origin. * * 5,997 (2010 Census) * 5,376 (2002 Census); * == Geography == The selo is located near the city of Omsk. == References == Category:Rural localities in Russia
title: Azovo, Omsk Oblast
